<subSubSection id="D6BCEE72A0835D81C3D53307F8CEE93C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="preliminary conservation assessment">
<paragraph id="139860EFB4FC61B0CF728798FF8B0AA0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Preliminary conservation assessment</paragraph>
<paragraph id="471E9B21A3EFB1EF44A9D0AAA68BE4A4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
(
<bibRefCitation id="E196A18FAF53CDB2303E19FA1CF758CB" author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="In: Aubreville A, Leroy J (Eds) Flore de La Nouvelle Caledonie et Dependances" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" refId="B13" refString="IUCN, 2019. Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" title="Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee." url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" year="2019">IUCN 2019</bibRefCitation>
). EOO = 0.25 km2 [CR - Critically Endangered]; AOO = 4 km2 [CR - Critically Endangered]. We assess 
<taxonomicName id="F63F308B1DEA8CE2A0F71DB28FD41C50" authorityName="D. McClelland, comb. et" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="F. Br." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum caumii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caumii">
<emphasis id="9C4273507BEDBE3CCABB533EB7883AAE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum caumii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as CR (Critically Endangered) using IUCN Criteria of B1,2a,b; populations may be secure on the isolated island of Nihoa that is largely protected, but no recent studies on population stability have been undertaken. Recognition of 
<taxonomicName id="DE5682784F98DFEDA36010DB67E364BB" genus="S." lsidName="S. caumii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="caumii">
<emphasis id="2314E11BD4B44F41C5EDE9D7DBA970C4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. caumii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at the species level has conservation consequences. 
<bibRefCitation id="4C7A289E1C82B673B8AAD37A2E358600" author="Symon, DE" editor="Wagner, WL" journalOrPublisher="2). University of Hawaii Press, Honolulu" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1251 - 1278" refId="B26" refString="Symon, DE, 1999. Solanaceae. In: Wagner, WL, Herbst, DR, Sohmer, SH, Eds., Manual of the Flowering Plants of Hawaii, revised edition (Vol. 2). University of Hawaii Press, Honolulu: 1251 - 1278" title="Solanaceae." volumeTitle="Manual of the Flowering Plants of Hawaii, revised edition (Vol." year="1999">Symon (1999)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName id="5619B8C5C3B82B656F78C976122272E8" genus="S." lsidName="S. caumii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="caumii">
<emphasis id="6D7F9B888934A9289BDDD10BA16E2A32" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. caumii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within 
<taxonomicName id="1FB90B0F62095393AD6A6A2D6086E35F" genus="S." lsidName="S. nelsonii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="nelsonii">
<emphasis id="D350037C558E5437595E4899631638BB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. nelsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. At that time 
<taxonomicName id="975BCAD23F89978E471D9B2291AB48B0" genus="S." lsidName="S. nelsonii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="nelsonii">
<emphasis id="A025F46437444081A2889849ECAB6629" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. nelsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was listed as vulnerable; segregation of 
<taxonomicName id="97E2C0168CA381A053E83BCBD67F0E27" genus="S." lsidName="S. caumii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="caumii">
<emphasis id="68F5C7140DDB5CB004A4A054EC702B3C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. caumii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the species may change the status of 
<taxonomicName id="2E780BEE644111B37BDC2DAB929A5DDE" genus="S." lsidName="S. nelsonii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="nelsonii">
<emphasis id="BC21DC86B3E607270394D6759D59D1B4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. nelsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Threats to 
<taxonomicName id="88A2B222252AD80B74FB8E95A9C4ED1D" genus="S." lsidName="S. caumii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="caumii">
<emphasis id="E74684465625B37A2AC2E8EF2E4FB770" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. caumii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
include habitat destruction from natural causes and herbivory by an introduced grasshopper (
<bibRefCitation id="0E115FE003ABD4EF7F12AE99F2722684" author="Mitchell, C" journalOrPublisher="Trends in Ecology &amp; Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B17" refString="Mitchell, C, Ogura, C, Meadows, DW, Kane, A, Strommer, L, Fretz, S, Leonard, D, McClung, A, 2005. Hawaii's Comprehensive Wildlife Conservation Strategy. Department of Land and Natural Resources, Honolulu." title="Hawaii's Comprehensive Wildlife Conservation Strategy. Department of Land and Natural Resources, Honolulu." year="2005">Mitchell et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="534F3FDA2469F5010164E000B673FDB2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="9DF777FE98E5395ADE635CDE3E9D65E8" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5DEC8653DA1CF8DF0A475949A9DFC013" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation id="1211C343F6FD8DF1D1D8E3EBDA5B4256" author="Brown, FBH" editor="Christophersen, E" journalOrPublisher="Bishop Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="35 - 37" refId="B7" refString="Brown, FBH, 1931. Solanaceae. In: Christophersen, E, Caum, EL, Eds., Vascular Plants of the Leeward Islands, Hawaii. Bulletin of the Bernice P. Bishop Museum 81: 35 - 37" title="Solanaceae." volume="81" volumeTitle="Vascular Plants of the Leeward Islands, Hawaii. Bulletin of the Bernice P." year="1931">Brown (1931)</bibRefCitation>
recognized the entity we here delimit as 
<taxonomicName id="002F7280CB087D9E8FB282F468D8AEA9" genus="S." lsidName="S. caumii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="caumii">
<emphasis id="0AEC0F4738AA7DBBEE899B48A94F1449" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. caumii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as two varieties of 
<taxonomicName id="27E9E13A15F632A5FC66706CB0676B92" genus="S." lsidName="S. nelsonii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="nelsonii">
<emphasis id="BC76A84D9E9FC5EA9560B2FB51B2E3C7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. nelsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a coastal species found on many islands in the Hawaiian archipelago. 
<bibRefCitation id="B78BBE2EB6600E7E5B9381254F2DEDA7" author="St John, H" journalOrPublisher="Trends in Ecology &amp; Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B22" refString="St John, H, 1988. Native Hawaiian species of Solanum (Solanaceae). Hawaiian Plant Studies 82. Published by the author, Honolulu." title="Native Hawaiian species of Solanum (Solanaceae). Hawaiian Plant Studies 82. Published by the author, Honolulu." year="1988">St. John (1988)</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName id="5E2A573EA1D464448F587B24E4246D74" genus="S." lsidName="S. nelsonii subsp. var. var. acuminatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="variety" species="nelsonii" subSpecies="var." variety="acuminatum">S. nelsonii var. acuminatum</taxonomicName>
in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="3E704DB55CB28AEBB9B82A4F16C297D9" genus="S." lsidName="S. nelsonii subsp. var. var. caumii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="variety" species="nelsonii" subSpecies="var." variety="caumii">S. nelsonii var. caumii</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="5D2972DE417CBC31D6CD3F3F009B865A" authorityName="D. McClelland, comb. et" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="F. Br." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum caumii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caumii">
<emphasis id="6975E92270B99DF741E33B72FEFE1C90" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum caumii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DFACE63901DC1468F32FED91CF0B3058" genus="S." lsidName="S. nelsonii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="nelsonii">
<emphasis id="7BECE49C6F8051E6BE3595C9770914C5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. nelsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but it can be distinguished by its semi-erect habit, larger leaf length to width ratio, and sometimes red fruit. In 2008, plants of 
<taxonomicName id="5FBD7D68A1F71A0DD9C386FDFE4C210B" genus="S." lsidName="S. nelsonii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="nelsonii">
<emphasis id="DDFE6377CF65E4B9179BD58C8BEB7CEB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. nelsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.s. from Molokai were cultivated alongside individuals from Nihoa (
<taxonomicName id="103D16CD57580AE30D91368BD6D870C6" genus="S." lsidName="S. caumii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="caumii">
<emphasis id="F1CA73C22749F743A4D991895F4B7298" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. caumii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) in greenhouses at the New York Botanical Garden (made available through the conservation program at the National Tropical Botanical Garden in Honolulu by Drs. David and Lida Burney and their staff). Under identical growing conditions plants here recognized as 
<taxonomicName id="A12DD7CF64A4E502C2B5FEC687ED34E2" genus="S." lsidName="S. caumii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="caumii">
<emphasis id="3AB032ABD0B325C780A47485489D739F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. caumii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="79C012809EF53D98679010066110C81E" genus="S." lsidName="S. nelsonii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="nelsonii">
<emphasis id="EF278EEBEAF0E97726917C47A8619D25" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. nelsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.s. maintained their distinct forms.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DB8B88329735BEE8710885A284667FC2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Endemism on the small island of Nihoa is relatively common, it is only one of four of the outer Hawaiian islands that still has exposed basalt substrate. There are other species of endemic or near-endemic plants (
<taxonomicName id="3EB9EADF9C79D13ECF971BCD4E212158" authorityName="Christoph &amp; Caum" authorityYear="1931" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Amaranthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Amaranthus brownii" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brownii">
<emphasis id="636C484A4C3DFC9CAEFB0BB6F48A47F7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Amaranthus brownii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Christoph. &amp; Caum, 
<taxonomicName id="25FBC999DAAA7D8E9B79B4A7A2F0C6FF" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Amaranthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Amaranthaceae</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="03028CCE2C056C3ED205CEE82B84FF5F" authorityName="Becc" authorityYear="1890" baseAuthorityName="Kuntze" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Pritchardia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pritchardia remota" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="remota">
<emphasis id="052841936D23EC55213CA861F4E7C290" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pritchardia remota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Becc., 
<taxonomicName id="B2DE1092EBF912424BF3DE3F65F6561A" class="Insecta" family="Arecaceae" genus="Pritchardia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Arecaceae</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="3DC043CC73B3736230A72228D0B87B07" genus="Scheidea" lsidName="Scheidea verticillata" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="verticillata">
<emphasis id="8C0804725823FC324639DD1FFE4EF77E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Scheidea verticillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
F.Br., 
<taxonomicName id="616A9CD43D259F0C0A93B1BF196F42BC" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Scheidea" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Caryophyllaceae</taxonomicName>
) and the entire island has been designated critical habitat for them (
<bibRefCitation id="6014951783A7D605D5EEAF46B4489386" author="Mitchell, C" journalOrPublisher="Trends in Ecology &amp; Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B17" refString="Mitchell, C, Ogura, C, Meadows, DW, Kane, A, Strommer, L, Fretz, S, Leonard, D, McClung, A, 2005. Hawaii's Comprehensive Wildlife Conservation Strategy. Department of Land and Natural Resources, Honolulu." title="Hawaii's Comprehensive Wildlife Conservation Strategy. Department of Land and Natural Resources, Honolulu." year="2005">Mitchell et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
). The island also hosts two endemic birds, at least seventeen endemic arthropods, and six endemic land snails (
<bibRefCitation id="C3B9F1D9EDB974D4E2A7116FE1A0B8D2" author="Mitchell, C" journalOrPublisher="Trends in Ecology &amp; Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B17" refString="Mitchell, C, Ogura, C, Meadows, DW, Kane, A, Strommer, L, Fretz, S, Leonard, D, McClung, A, 2005. Hawaii's Comprehensive Wildlife Conservation Strategy. Department of Land and Natural Resources, Honolulu." title="Hawaii's Comprehensive Wildlife Conservation Strategy. Department of Land and Natural Resources, Honolulu." year="2005">Mitchell et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
